"n.极度激动的状态，狂暴 【英】 n.极度激动的状态(st ate of extreme excitement) 【考】 convulsion : contraction / frenzy : emotion(痉挛是收缩加剧/疯 狂是感情加剧) 【例】 in a frenzy of zeal, enthusiasm, hate n. 狂乱(极度激动的状态) = delirium = mania 【类】convulsion: contraction = frenzy: emotion痉挛是收缩加剧 = 疯狂是感情加剧frenzy: calm[calmness] = abandon: prohibit[inhibition]狂暴: 使平静 = 放任: 禁止(反义) 【记】音：疯子 frenzy (n.)  mid-14c., ""delirium, insanity,"" from Old French frenesie, from Medieval Latin phrenesia, from phrenesis, back-formation from Latin phreneticus ""delirious"" (see frenetic). Meaning ""excited state of mind"" is from c.1400."
